          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397782-fullscreenminheight"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property applies only to an "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSTitlebarAccessoryViewController"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object in which "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397778-layoutattribute"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/nslayoutattribute/nslayoutattributebottom"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The minimum height you set determines how much of your accessory view is visible when the menu bar is hidden during full screen mode. By default, the minimum height is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which means that the accessory view is hidden when the menu bar is hidden. When a user reveals the menu bar in this scenario, the accessory view is also revealed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To persistently show a portion of the accessory view, set this property to a value greater than "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". For example, if you have a fixed height accessory view, you can set "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397782-fullscreenminheight"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "view.frame.size.height"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to show the view regardless of whether the menu bar is hidden. Note that the view's height is never actually changed when it is hidden or revealed; instead, it is automatically clipped by an internal clip view."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
